{
  "texts": [
    "Three main aspects factor into the wide transferability of our framework.",
    "First, the ecosys model, which provides the scientific foundation for KGML-ag-Carbon, is a well-validated advanced agroecosystem model with detailed process representation for simulating complex interactions among carbon, nutrients, water, and energy cycles 13, 29, 54, 55.",
    "Various studies have demonstrated its global capability for simulating crop ecosystems 13, natural ecosystems 54, and management practice impacts [56] [57] [58] [59].",
    "Thus, ecosys can continue to generate abundant synthetic data for pre-training the model to adapt specific pathways from input variables to target variables.",
    "Second, assimilating multi-source data can extend the framework to larger regions and more ecosystem types 15, 25, 27, 60."
  ]
}